  "doc_id": "2044",
  "text": "industrial applications, and as such, come in different sizes, shapes, chemical compositions, and crystalline structures. [CITATION_1] TiO 2 occurs in four crystalline polymorphic forms, of which rutile and anatase are the most common. [CITATION_2] Rutile is considered to be a more inert form whereas anatase is an active form of TiO [CITATION_3] . Some studies indicate that anatase TiO 2 nanoparticles are more cytotoxic than rutile TiO 2 nanoparticles. [CITATION_4] Yeo et al [CITATION_5] have reported that different TiO 2 nanoparticles induce different toxicities during embryogenesis of the zebra fish due to their different sizes and crystalline phases. The increased use of nanoparticles is a matter of great concern to health professionals and environmental scientists because of the potential risks to humans and to the environment. [CITATION_6] Of the possible exposure routes, inhalation and skin contact are considered to be the most important for nanoparticles. The toxic effects of nanoparticles can be attributed to their small size and hence large surface area, which increases their chemical reactivity and penetration into living cells.",
